{
  "texts": [
    "We also performed an ablation study with and without three channel features, as shown in Table 5.",
    "The performance is depicted in Fig. 8, where we evaluate the efficiency of these features in building unrelated graphs.",
    "The absence of syntactic feature information led to decreased accuracy across all three datasets, with H-GIN particularly affected.",
    "However, the overall performance decrease was relatively small, emphasizing the importance of syntactic features in contextual information capture.",
    "Meanwhile, the absence of semantic features significantly decreases the model accuracy across all datasets, especially in PTC and Qprop, where word structure is prevalent."
  ]
}